27/05/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in Kavaja completed a six-month investigation on an international drug smuggling ring and arrested six people Thursday (May 26th). About 26kg of marijuana, vehicles, guns and ammunition were seized during a raid on a private property. Investigators say the suspects were receiving the marijuana supply from the southern village of Lazarat and prepared it for international markets. The group will be charged with drug trafficking and illegal weapon possession. (Balkan Web, Lajmifundit, Top News, Ora News - 26/05/11)
